    "summarization": {
        "a": "This figure tracks the desorption of nitrogen (N, m/z = 14) and carbon-related impurities (CO, CO\u2082) from indium, gallium, and zinc oxide films during heating. For indium oxide, the N\u2082O plasma treatment (blue line) significantly suppresses CO and CO\u2082 desorption in the 350\u2013500 \u00b0C range (yellow boxes) compared to the O\u2082 reference (black line), demonstrating more effective removal of carbon-based ligand residues.",
        "b": "Gallium oxide uniquely exhibits a high-temperature nitrogen release (yellow box, inset) after N\u2082O treatment, confirming stable nitrogen incorporation into the Ga\u2082O\u2083 lattice and supporting the improved stability observed in prior electrical measurements.",
        "c": "Zinc oxide temperature-dependent desorption of species, measured using TDS at m/z = 14, 28, and 44."
    },
